Samsung recently launched its new mid-range smartphone in South Africa – the Galaxy A Series. The smartphones sport the company’s Infinity-U display design, which comprises a bezel-less panel with a cutout at the top of the screen for a single camera. Samsung has also merged its J Series devices into the A Series, resulting in a range of handsets priced from as low as R1,299 all the way up to R12,999. The recommended retail pricing for the A Series smartphones is below. Many of these smartphones are also available on contract from local mobile operators – and we have listed the best deals below. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-304070" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Samsung-Galaxy-A2-Core.jpg" alt="Samsung Galaxy A2 Core" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Samsung-Galaxy-A2-Core.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Samsung-Galaxy-A2-Core-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Samsung-Galaxy-A2-Core-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-304072" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Samsung-Galaxy-A10.jpg" alt="Samsung Galaxy A10" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Samsung-Galaxy-A10.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Samsung-Galaxy-A10-300x202.jpg 300w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Samsung-Galaxy-A10-595x400.jpg 595w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-304074" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Samsung-Galaxy-A20.jpg" alt="Samsung Galaxy A20" width="640" height="430" srcset=